# Smart Go Clean Code Rules

- Keep code clean and modular: separate `constants`, `enums`, `interfaces`, `decorators`, `services`, and `interceptors` into dedicated files/folders.
- Follow existing project structure and naming conventions before introducing new files.
- Prefer endpoint-scoped behavior over global behavior when requirement is per API.

# Config and Environment Rules

- Keep only necessary config keys; remove unused flags and dead config.
- Put encryption secrets/algorithm in env config; avoid hardcoding secrets in business logic.
- Update `.env.example` whenever env keys are added/removed.

# Code Quality Rules

- Prefer small, single-responsibility classes/functions.
- Remove dead code/imports/files after refactor.
- Keep formatting consistent with repository style and run build/lint checks after significant changes.
